{"source_type": "idea", "source_id": "auction-dynamic-paradox", "source_display": "The Auction Dynamic Paradox", "relation": "originated_by", "target_type": "person", "target_id": "ray", "target_display": "Ray", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-15-2026-01-15-trio-standup", "evidence": "Ray's advice—'If you only have one, don't expect to make any money'—reveals that acquisition value is created primarily by competition, not by the intrinsic value of what's being sold.", "evolution_type": null}
{"source_type": "idea", "source_id": "fomo-as-product", "source_display": "FOMO as Product (M&A)", "relation": "supports", "target_type": "idea", "target_id": "auction-dynamic-paradox", "target_display": "The Auction Dynamic Paradox", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-15-2026-01-15-trio-standup", "evidence": "In M&A, you're not selling a company. You're selling the fear of losing it to a competitor. The product is FOMO, not technology.", "evolution_type": null}
{"source_type": "idea", "source_id": "earnout-trap-thesis", "source_display": "The Earnout Trap (Aligned Incentives Gone Wrong)", "relation": "originated_by", "target_type": "person", "target_id": "ray", "target_display": "Ray", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-15-2026-01-15-trio-standup", "evidence": "Ray's experience shows acquirers can manipulate success metrics, making earnouts a one-sided bet. Ray's experience: potential $1M became $50-100K.", "evolution_type": null}
{"source_type": "idea", "source_id": "risk-transfer-disguised-as-alignment", "source_display": "Risk Transfer Disguised as Alignment", "relation": "supports", "target_type": "idea", "target_id": "earnout-trap-thesis", "target_display": "The Earnout Trap", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-15-2026-01-15-trio-standup", "evidence": "What looks like incentive alignment is often risk transfer. When the party defining success metrics is the same party measuring them, 'alignment' becomes a polite word for 'control.'", "evolution_type": null}
{"source_type": "decision", "source_id": "salary-over-earnouts", "source_display": "Negotiate Salary Over Earnouts", "relation": "implements", "target_type": "idea", "target_id": "earnout-trap-thesis", "target_display": "The Earnout Trap", "context_meeting_id": "mtg_2026-01-15-2026-01-15-trio-standup", "evidence": "In acquisition negotiations, optimize for salary and bonuses rather than earnout structures. Salary is contractually guaranteed.", "evolution_type": null}
